Okay, for equipment: 

There should be 3 types of inventory item - Rumors, Luggage and Consumables.

Consumables simply provide a number of consumable things (like heals and Lex replenishment) for the course of a mission.

Rumors unlock an Agent's equipment and new Agents. Each new equipment unlock should be a binary choice, and each Agent should have a finite number of rumors to generate equipment from. Agents should end-up with enough gear to cover all their slots plus a bit extra for build variety / mission specialization. Agent unlocks should not be binary.

There should be some hidden rumors for Agents to find.

Luggage generates the game's currency(s) to spend between missions.

All slot items simply work via the XP system - they gain XP with the Agent carrying them, converting it into their own special resource (Loot and Intelligence), and sometimes gain large quantities of their own resource as a bonus. 

Each Agent should have 10 Rumours, and each rumour should have 2 equipment unlocks and an Agent unlock (until we run out of Agents).

That'll provide 20 pieces of gear per run; plenty to play around with builds. There should probably be 2 gear sets, with 4 pieces to each. 

Agents should start the game with enough equipment to provide them with interesting options, but also a bunch of discoverable equipment hidden on missions. The split should perhaps be 50/50 ? The hidden stuff should just be cool. 




